sed upon entitlement to basic pay.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (f), the words “provided by law”, “this or any other”, and “for any reason” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (g), the words “Judge Advocate General of the Navy” are inserted to reflect ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s5148"},"text":"section 5148 of title 10","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (i), the last 12 words of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s5145/c"},"text":"section 5145(c) of title 10","children":[],"tail":" are omitted as covered by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s5134"},"text":"section 5134 of title 10","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb057832e-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb057832f-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1985—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/145"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–145","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Pay grades: retired Coast Guard rear admirals (lower half)” for “Pay grade: retired Coast Guard commodores” in section catchline, and substituted “rear admiral (lower half)” for “commodore” in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Pay grade: retired Coast Guard commodores” for “Pay grades: commodores, retired list” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/417"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–417","children":[],"tail":" substituted provision relating to the entitlement of retired list Coast Guard commodores to the basic pay of a retired rear admiral after two years emergency or wartime duty, for former subsecs. (a) and (b), which, respectively, related to the entitlement of retired Coast Guard rear admirals (otherwise entitled to the basic pay of retired list rear admirals) to the basic pay of an upper half rear admiral after two years emergency or wartime active duty, and provided that the number of active list Coast Guard rear admirals entitled to upper half pay be half the difference between the number of active list officers above captain and the number of officers serving above rear admiral, an odd number result to be placed in the upper half, and no officer entitled to rear admiral pay to have it reduced solely because of a reduction in the number of rear admirals."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s401/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 401(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “(upper half) of the Coast Guard” for “of upper half; officers holding certain positions in the Navy” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s401/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 401(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), redesignated subsec. (e) as (a) and struck out applicability to the Navy. Former subsec. (a), relating to entitlement of an officer not restricted in the performance of his duties in the Navy, was struck out."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/s401/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, § 401(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated subsec. (f) as (b). Former subsec. (b), relating to 